menu "Dormer Window State Configuration"

    config WINDOW_SENSOR_GPIO
        int "Window contact sensor GPIO pin"
        default 4
        range 0 30
        help
            Digital input GPIO connected to the reed switch / magnetic contact
            sensor mounted on the window and frame.

    config WINDOW_SENSOR_ACTIVE_LOW
        bool "Sensor reads LOW when window is closed"
        default y
        help
            Most reed switches short the pin to GND when the magnet is present
            (window closed), so with an internal pull-up the pin reads LOW when
            closed and HIGH when open. Disable this if your wiring is inverted
            (e.g. switch wired to 3.3V with a pull-down instead).

    config WINDOW_SENSOR_DEBOUNCE_MS
        int "Debounce time (milliseconds)"
        default 50
        range 5 1000
        help
            Time the pin level must remain stable after an edge before the
            new state is trusted and pushed to the Matter Boolean State
            attribute. Increase if the reed switch is mechanically noisy.

endmenu
